{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RXrtxrHyvFHWTvzWaxsnDN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the full picture. Looking at the acceptance criteria for US-002:\n\n1. **Router maps events to stages** - The existing `detectStage` already does most of this, but the AC specifies `re-triage` for issue_comment events (currently returns \"triage\"), and `release` for the final stage (currently \"ship\"). Let me re-read the AC carefully.\n\nThe AC says:\n- `issue_comment.created` (if issue has `kiln:intake` or `kiln:needs-info`) → **re-triage** (current: returns \"triage\")\n- `pull_request_review.submitted approved` or `check_suite.completed` on impl PR → **release** (current: returns \"ship\")\n\nWait, looking more carefully at the PRD, the stage names used in the AC are just descriptions of what happens. The actual stage handler names in `index.ts` are: `triage`, `specify`, `approve-spec`, `implement`, `review`, `fix`, `ship`. The AC says the router should map to specific stages — let me compare:\n\n- `issues.opened` → triage ✓\n- `issue_comment.created` (intake/needs-info) → re-triage. Currently returns \"triage\" but AC says \"re-triage\"\n- `issues.labeled` (kiln:specifying) → specify ✓\n- `pull_request_review.submitted` approved + spec PR → approve-spec ✓\n- `issues.labeled` (kiln:implementing) → implement ✓\n- `pull_request.opened` or `pull_request.synchronize` + impl PR → review ✓\n- `pull_request_review.submitted` changes_requested + impl PR → fix ✓\n- `pull_request_review.submitted` approved + impl PR → release (current: \"ship\")\n- `check_suite.completed` + impl PR → release (current: \"ship\")\n\n2. **Unmatched events → clean no-op exit** - Already handled (returns null → index.ts exits cleanly)\n3. **Router logs which stage it selected** - Not currently logging\n4. **Router passes parsed context** - The router currently returns just a string. The AC wants it to pass parsed context (issue number, PR number, labels, event payload) to the selected stage handler.\n\nLet me look at how the stages currently receive context - they get the full `KilnContext` which includes `context` (the GitHub Actions context with full payload). So the \"parsed context\" requirement might mean the router should extract and return structured context alongside the stage name.\n\nLet me re-read the AC more carefully and look at the stages to understand what context they need."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":279,"cache_read_input_tokens":33863,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":279},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"942cf364-60e4-40c3-bc94-9e511a2c0dff","uuid":"4d40db48-3069-4554-92f8-35d1550048b9"}
