{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SyjYm34cj9RicwxnyzQd1d","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import * as core from \"@actions/core\";\n     2→import * as fs from \"fs\";\n     3→import { execSync } from \"child_process\";\n     4→import { runClaudeEdit } from \"../claude\";\n     5→import { transitionLabel } from \"../labels\";\n     6→import { KilnContext, StageResult } from \"../types\";\n     7→\n     8→const DEFAULT_SPEC_TEMPLATE = `# Spec: [Title]\n     9→\n    10→## 1. Overview\n    11→What this change does and why it's needed.\n    12→\n    13→## 2. Requirements\n    14→- [ ] Acceptance criterion 1\n    15→- [ ] Acceptance criterion 2\n    16→- [ ] Acceptance criterion 3\n    17→\n    18→## 3. Technical Design\n    19→\n    20→### Files to create/modify\n    21→| File | Action | Purpose |\n    22→|---|---|---|\n    23→| path/to/file | create/modify | description |\n    24→\n    25→### Key interfaces / types\n    26→\\`\\`\\`typescript\n    27→// Define key interfaces here\n    28→\\`\\`\\`\n    29→\n    30→### Data flow\n    31→Describe how data moves through the system.\n    32→\n    33→### Edge cases\n    34→- Edge case 1\n    35→- Edge case 2\n    36→\n    37→## 4. Test Plan\n    38→\n    39→### Unit tests\n    40→- Test case 1\n    41→- Test case 2\n    42→\n    43→### Integration tests\n    44→- Test case 1\n    45→\n    46→### Manual verification\n    47→- Step 1\n    48→- Step 2\n    49→\n    50→## 5. Out of Scope\n    51→What this change does NOT cover.\n    52→\n    53→## 6. Implementation Notes\n    54→- Suggested order of implementation\n    55→- Potential pitfalls or gotchas\n    56→`;\n    57→\n    58→export default async function specify(\n    59→  ctx: KilnContext,\n    60→): Promise<StageResult> {\n    61→  const { octokit, context, config, anthropicKey, timeoutMinutes } = ctx;\n    62→  const issue = context.payload.issue!;\n    63→  const prefix = config.labels?.prefix || \"kiln\";\n    64→  const issueNum = issue.number;\n    65→  const branchName = `kiln/spec/issue-${issueNum}`;\n    66→\n    67→  core.info(`🔥 Specify — Issue #${issueNum}: ${issue.title}`);\n    68→\n    69→  execSync('git config user.name \"kiln[bot]\"');\n    70→  execSync('git config user.email \"kiln[bot]@users.noreply.github.com\"');\n    71→  execSync(`git checkout -b ${branchName}`);\n    72→\n    73→  fs.mkdirSync(\"specs\", { recursive: true });\n    74→\n    75→  let specTemplate = DEFAULT_SPEC_TEMPLATE;\n    76→  const templatePath =\n    77→    config.spec_template || config.agents?.spec?.template;\n    78→  if (templatePath && fs.existsSync(templatePath)) {\n    79→    specTemplate = fs.readFileSync(templatePath, \"utf-8\");\n    80→    core.info(`🔥 Using custom spec template: ${templatePath}`);\n    81→  }\n    82→\n    83→  const prompt = `You are the Kiln spec agent. Your job is to produce a detailed, implementable specification.\n    84→\n    85→**Issue #${issueNum}**\n    86→**Title:** ${issue.title}\n    87→**Body:** ${issue.body || \"(empty)\"}\n    88→\n    89→First, read the existing codebase to understand the project structure, conventions, tech stack, and patterns.\n    90→\n    91→Then create the spec file at: specs/issue-${issueNum}.md\n    92→\n    93→Use this structure for the spec:\n    94→\n    95→${specTemplate}\n    96→\n    97→Important:\n    98→- Be specific about which files to create or modify\n    99→- Include concrete type/interface definitions where relevant\n   100→- Acceptance criteria must be testable\n   101→- Reference existing patterns in the codebase\n   102→- The implementation agent will use this spec as its SOLE instruction set\n   103→\n   104→After creating the spec file, commit it to the current branch with message:\n   105→\"docs: add spec for issue #${issueNum}\"\n   106→\n   107→Then push the branch.`;\n   108→\n   109→  runClaudeEdit(prompt, { anthropicKey, timeoutMinutes });\n   110→\n   111→  const specPath = `specs/issue-${issueNum}.md`;\n   112→  if (!fs.existsSync(specPath)) {\n   113→    core.setFailed(`Spec agent did not create ${specPath}`);\n   114→    return { status: \"error\" };\n   115→  }\n   116→\n   117→  try {\n   118→    execSync(\n   119→      `git add -A && git commit -m \"docs: add spec for issue #${issueNum}\" --allow-empty`,\n   120→    );\n   121→  } catch {\n   122→    // Already committed by Claude\n   123→  }\n   124→  execSync(`git push origin ${branchName} --force`);\n   125→\n   126→  const { data: pr } = await octokit.rest.pulls.create({\n   127→    ...context.repo,\n   128→    title: `📋 Kiln Spec: ${issue.title}`,\n   129→    body: [\n   130→      `## Specification for #${issueNum}`,\n   131→      \"\",\n   132→      \"🔥 *Fired in the Kiln*\",\n   133→      \"\",\n   134→      `Review the spec at \\`${specPath}\\`.`,\n   135→      \"**Approve this PR to trigger implementation.**\",\n   136→      \"\",\n   137→      \"---\",\n   138→      `Tracking issue: #${issueNum}`,\n   139→    ].join(\"\\n\"),\n   140→    head: branchName,\n   141→    base: \"main\",\n   142→  });\n   143→\n   144→  await octokit.rest.issues.addLabels({\n   145→    ...context.repo,\n   146→    issue_number: pr.number,\n   147→    labels: [`${prefix}:spec`, \"needs-human-review\"],\n   148→  });\n   149→\n   150→  await octokit.rest.issues.createComment({\n   151→    ...context.repo,\n   152→    issue_number: issueNum,\n   153→    body: `📋 **Kiln** — Spec ready for review: #${pr.number}\\n\\nApprove the spec PR to start implementation.`,\n   154→  });\n   155→\n   156→  await transitionLabel(\n   157→    octokit,\n   158→    context,\n   159→    issueNum,\n   160→    \"specifying\",\n   161→    \"spec-review\",\n   162→    prefix,\n   163→  );\n   164→\n   165→  return { status: \"success\", prNumber: pr.number };\n   166→}\n   167→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"942cf364-60e4-40c3-bc94-9e511a2c0dff","uuid":"c628af6d-1c65-4e08-b0c1-99cad87fbab6","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/marlinf/Projects/datashaman/kiln-action/src/stages/specify.ts","content":"import * as core from \"@actions/core\";\nimport * as fs from \"fs\";\nimport { execSync } from \"child_process\";\nimport { runClaudeEdit } from \"../claude\";\nimport { transitionLabel } from \"../labels\";\nimport { KilnContext, StageResult } from \"../types\";\n\nconst DEFAULT_SPEC_TEMPLATE = `# Spec: [Title]\n\n## 1. Overview\nWhat this change does and why it's needed.\n\n## 2. Requirements\n- [ ] Acceptance criterion 1\n- [ ] Acceptance criterion 2\n- [ ] Acceptance criterion 3\n\n## 3. Technical Design\n\n### Files to create/modify\n| File | Action | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| path/to/file | create/modify | description |\n\n### Key interfaces / types\n\\`\\`\\`typescript\n// Define key interfaces here\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Data flow\nDescribe how data moves through the system.\n\n### Edge cases\n- Edge case 1\n- Edge case 2\n\n## 4. Test Plan\n\n### Unit tests\n- Test case 1\n- Test case 2\n\n### Integration tests\n- Test case 1\n\n### Manual verification\n- Step 1\n- Step 2\n\n## 5. Out of Scope\nWhat this change does NOT cover.\n\n## 6. Implementation Notes\n- Suggested order of implementation\n- Potential pitfalls or gotchas\n`;\n\nexport default async function specify(\n  ctx: KilnContext,\n): Promise<StageResult> {\n  const { octokit, context, config, anthropicKey, timeoutMinutes } = ctx;\n  const issue = context.payload.issue!;\n  const prefix = config.labels?.prefix || \"kiln\";\n  const issueNum = issue.number;\n  const branchName = `kiln/spec/issue-${issueNum}`;\n\n  core.info(`🔥 Specify — Issue #${issueNum}: ${issue.title}`);\n\n  execSync('git config user.name \"kiln[bot]\"');\n  execSync('git config user.email \"kiln[bot]@users.noreply.github.com\"');\n  execSync(`git checkout -b ${branchName}`);\n\n  fs.mkdirSync(\"specs\", { recursive: true });\n\n  let specTemplate = DEFAULT_SPEC_TEMPLATE;\n  const templatePath =\n    config.spec_template || config.agents?.spec?.template;\n  if (templatePath && fs.existsSync(templatePath)) {\n    specTemplate = fs.readFileSync(templatePath, \"utf-8\");\n    core.info(`🔥 Using custom spec template: ${templatePath}`);\n  }\n\n  const prompt = `You are the Kiln spec agent. Your job is to produce a detailed, implementable specification.\n\n**Issue #${issueNum}**\n**Title:** ${issue.title}\n**Body:** ${issue.body || \"(empty)\"}\n\nFirst, read the existing codebase to understand the project structure, conventions, tech stack, and patterns.\n\nThen create the spec file at: specs/issue-${issueNum}.md\n\nUse this structure for the spec:\n\n${specTemplate}\n\nImportant:\n- Be specific about which files to create or modify\n- Include concrete type/interface definitions where relevant\n- Acceptance criteria must be testable\n- Reference existing patterns in the codebase\n- The implementation agent will use this spec as its SOLE instruction set\n\nAfter creating the spec file, commit it to the current branch with message:\n\"docs: add spec for issue #${issueNum}\"\n\nThen push the branch.`;\n\n  runClaudeEdit(prompt, { anthropicKey, timeoutMinutes });\n\n  const specPath = `specs/issue-${issueNum}.md`;\n  if (!fs.existsSync(specPath)) {\n    core.setFailed(`Spec agent did not create ${specPath}`);\n    return { status: \"error\" };\n  }\n\n  try {\n    execSync(\n      `git add -A && git commit -m \"docs: add spec for issue #${issueNum}\" --allow-empty`,\n    );\n  } catch {\n    // Already committed by Claude\n  }\n  execSync(`git push origin ${branchName} --force`);\n\n  const { data: pr } = await octokit.rest.pulls.create({\n    ...context.repo,\n    title: `📋 Kiln Spec: ${issue.title}`,\n    body: [\n      `## Specification for #${issueNum}`,\n      \"\",\n      \"🔥 *Fired in the Kiln*\",\n      \"\",\n      `Review the spec at \\`${specPath}\\`.`,\n      \"**Approve this PR to trigger implementation.**\",\n      \"\",\n      \"---\",\n      `Tracking issue: #${issueNum}`,\n    ].join(\"\\n\"),\n    head: branchName,\n    base: \"main\",\n  });\n\n  await octokit.rest.issues.addLabels({\n    ...context.repo,\n    issue_number: pr.number,\n    labels: [`${prefix}:spec`, \"needs-human-review\"],\n  });\n\n  await octokit.rest.issues.createComment({\n    ...context.repo,\n    issue_number: issueNum,\n    body: `📋 **Kiln** — Spec ready for review: #${pr.number}\\n\\nApprove the spec PR to start implementation.`,\n  });\n\n  await transitionLabel(\n    octokit,\n    context,\n    issueNum,\n    \"specifying\",\n    \"spec-review\",\n    prefix,\n  );\n\n  return { status: \"success\", prNumber: pr.number };\n}\n","numLines":167,"startLine":1,"totalLines":167}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XABb2VJZGYmJXzJRddZkr8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import * as core from \"@actions/core\";\n     2→import { transitionLabel } from \"../labels\";\n     3→import { KilnContext, StageResult } from \"../types\";\n     4→\n     5→export default async function ship(ctx: KilnContext): Promise<StageResult> {\n     6→  const { octokit, context, config } = ctx;\n     7→  const pr = context.payload.pull_request;\n     8→  const prefix = config.labels?.prefix || \"kiln\";\n     9→\n    10→  if (!pr) {\n    11→    core.info(\"🔥 Ship — No PR in payload, skipping.\");\n    12→    return { status: \"skipped\" };\n    13→  }\n    14→\n    15→  core.info(`🔥 Ship — Checking if PR #${pr.number} is ready to merge`);\n    16→\n    17→  const { data: reviews } = await octokit.rest.pulls.listReviews({\n    18→    ...context.repo,\n    19→    pull_number: pr.number,\n    20→  });\n    21→\n    22→  const isApproved = reviews.some((r) => r.state === \"APPROVED\");\n    23→  if (!isApproved) {\n    24→    core.info(\"🔥 Ship — PR not yet approved. Skipping.\");\n    25→    return { status: \"skipped\", reason: \"not-approved\" };\n    26→  }\n    27→\n    28→  const { data: checks } = await octokit.rest.checks.listForRef({\n    29→    ...context.repo,\n    30→    ref: pr.head.sha,\n    31→  });\n    32→\n    33→  const ciPassing = checks.check_runs\n    34→    .filter((c) => c.name !== \"kiln\")\n    35→    .every(\n    36→      (c) =>\n    37→        c.conclusion === \"success\" ||\n    38→        c.conclusion === \"skipped\" ||\n    39→        c.status === \"queued\",\n    40→    );\n    41→\n    42→  if (!ciPassing) {\n    43→    core.info(\n    44→      \"🔥 Ship — CI not yet green. Will retry when checks complete.\",\n    45→    );\n    46→    return { status: \"skipped\", reason: \"ci-pending\" };\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  if (!config.auto_merge) {\n    50→    core.info(\n    51→      \"🔥 Ship — Auto-merge disabled. PR is approved and ready for manual merge.\",\n    52→    );\n    53→    await octokit.rest.issues.createComment({\n    54→      ...context.repo,\n    55→      issue_number: pr.number,\n    56→      body: \"✅ **Kiln** — PR approved and CI green. Auto-merge is disabled — merge when ready.\",\n    57→    });\n    58→    return { status: \"success\", reason: \"auto-merge-disabled\" };\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  core.info(`🔥 Ship — Merging PR #${pr.number}`);\n    62→\n    63→  try {\n    64→    await octokit.rest.pulls.merge({\n    65→      ...context.repo,\n    66→      pull_number: pr.number,\n    67→      merge_method: \"squash\",\n    68→      commit_title: `${pr.title} (#${pr.number})`,\n    69→    });\n    70→  } catch (error) {\n    71→    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n    72→    core.warning(`Merge failed: ${message}`);\n    73→    return { status: \"error\", reason: \"merge-failed\" };\n    74→  }\n    75→\n    76→  const issueMatch = (pr.body as string | undefined)?.match(/Closes #(\\d+)/);\n    77→  if (issueMatch) {\n    78→    const issueNumber = parseInt(issueMatch[1], 10);\n    79→\n    80→    await transitionLabel(\n    81→      octokit,\n    82→      context,\n    83→      issueNumber,\n    84→      \"in-review\",\n    85→      \"done\",\n    86→      prefix,\n    87→    );\n    88→\n    89→    await octokit.rest.issues.update({\n    90→      ...context.repo,\n    91→      issue_number: issueNumber,\n    92→      state: \"closed\",\n    93→    });\n    94→\n    95→    await octokit.rest.issues.createComment({\n    96→      ...context.repo,\n    97→      issue_number: issueNumber,\n    98→      body: [\n    99→        \"🔥 **Kiln** — Shipped!\",\n   100→        \"\",\n   101→        `Implementation merged via #${pr.number}.`,\n   102→        \"\",\n   103→        \"*Fired in the Kiln.* 🏷️\",\n   104→      ].join(\"\\n\"),\n   105→    });\n   106→\n   107→    core.info(`🔥 Ship — Issue #${issueNumber} closed.`);\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  core.info(\"🔥 Shipped! 🚀\");\n   111→  return { status: \"success\" };\n   112→}\n   113→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"942cf364-60e4-40c3-bc94-9e511a2c0dff","uuid":"0624903d-2eba-4f90-bf81-ba424deceb1d","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/marlinf/Projects/datashaman/kiln-action/src/stages/ship.ts","content":"import * as core from \"@actions/core\";\nimport { transitionLabel } from \"../labels\";\nimport { KilnContext, StageResult } from \"../types\";\n\nexport default async function ship(ctx: KilnContext): Promise<StageResult> {\n  const { octokit, context, config } = ctx;\n  const pr = context.payload.pull_request;\n  const prefix = config.labels?.prefix || \"kiln\";\n\n  if (!pr) {\n    core.info(\"🔥 Ship — No PR in payload, skipping.\");\n    return { status: \"skipped\" };\n  }\n\n  core.info(`🔥 Ship — Checking if PR #${pr.number} is ready to merge`);\n\n  const { data: reviews } = await octokit.rest.pulls.listReviews({\n    ...context.repo,\n    pull_number: pr.number,\n  });\n\n  const isApproved = reviews.some((r) => r.state === \"APPROVED\");\n  if (!isApproved) {\n    core.info(\"🔥 Ship — PR not yet approved. Skipping.\");\n    return { status: \"skipped\", reason: \"not-approved\" };\n  }\n\n  const { data: checks } = await octokit.rest.checks.listForRef({\n    ...context.repo,\n    ref: pr.head.sha,\n  });\n\n  const ciPassing = checks.check_runs\n    .filter((c) => c.name !== \"kiln\")\n    .every(\n      (c) =>\n        c.conclusion === \"success\" ||\n        c.conclusion === \"skipped\" ||\n        c.status === \"queued\",\n    );\n\n  if (!ciPassing) {\n    core.info(\n      \"🔥 Ship — CI not yet green. Will retry when checks complete.\",\n    );\n    return { status: \"skipped\", reason: \"ci-pending\" };\n  }\n\n  if (!config.auto_merge) {\n    core.info(\n      \"🔥 Ship — Auto-merge disabled. PR is approved and ready for manual merge.\",\n    );\n    await octokit.rest.issues.createComment({\n      ...context.repo,\n      issue_number: pr.number,\n      body: \"✅ **Kiln** — PR approved and CI green. Auto-merge is disabled — merge when ready.\",\n    });\n    return { status: \"success\", reason: \"auto-merge-disabled\" };\n  }\n\n  core.info(`🔥 Ship — Merging PR #${pr.number}`);\n\n  try {\n    await octokit.rest.pulls.merge({\n      ...context.repo,\n      pull_number: pr.number,\n      merge_method: \"squash\",\n      commit_title: `${pr.title} (#${pr.number})`,\n    });\n  } catch (error) {\n    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n    core.warning(`Merge failed: ${message}`);\n    return { status: \"error\", reason: \"merge-failed\" };\n  }\n\n  const issueMatch = (pr.body as string | undefined)?.match(/Closes #(\\d+)/);\n  if (issueMatch) {\n    const issueNumber = parseInt(issueMatch[1], 10);\n\n    await transitionLabel(\n      octokit,\n      context,\n      issueNumber,\n      \"in-review\",\n      \"done\",\n      prefix,\n    );\n\n    await octokit.rest.issues.update({\n      ...context.repo,\n      issue_number: issueNumber,\n      state: \"closed\",\n    });\n\n    await octokit.rest.issues.createComment({\n      ...context.repo,\n      issue_number: issueNumber,\n      body: [\n        \"🔥 **Kiln** — Shipped!\",\n        \"\",\n        `Implementation merged via #${pr.number}.`,\n        \"\",\n        \"*Fired in the Kiln.* 🏷️\",\n      ].join(\"\\n\"),\n    });\n\n    core.info(`🔥 Ship — Issue #${issueNumber} closed.`);\n  }\n\n  core.info(\"🔥 Shipped! 🚀\");\n  return { status: \"success\" };\n}\n","numLines":113,"startLine":1,"totalLines":113}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019qonnYZyp38stHRrhrVcDS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. For US-002, looking at the acceptance criteria:\n\n1. The router needs to return the correct stage names per the AC mapping. The AC uses \"re-triage\" and \"release\" as stage names, but the existing STAGES map in `index.ts` uses \"triage\" and \"ship\". I need to align the router with the AC.\n2. The router needs to **log** which stage it selected.\n3. The router needs to **pass parsed context** to the stage handler.\n4. Unmatched events need a clean no-op.\n\nLooking at this more carefully, the AC names (`re-triage`, `release`) are descriptive stage names in the PRD. But the codebase has handlers named `triage` and `ship`. Since US-002 is about the router specifically, I should:\n- Make the router return the correct stage names that match the AC\n- Update `index.ts` STAGES map accordingly to handle the new stage names\n- Add logging to the router\n- Add parsed context to the router return\n\nLet me implement this. I'll update the router to return a `RouteResult` object with stage name, parsed context, and add logging. I'll also need to update `index.ts` to handle the new return type and the re-triage/release stage name mappings.\n\nActually, looking again at the AC more carefully: \"re-triage\" maps to the same triage handler but for issue comments. And \"release\" maps to the ship handler. The simplest approach that satisfies the AC while keeping the codebase working: update the router to return these exact stage names, and update the STAGES map in index.ts to map them to the existing handlers.\n\nLet me also add the parsed context (RouterContext) that the AC requires."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5401,"cache_read_input_tokens":34142,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens