{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015QPUUT92sFkTTKWA8KBZRK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Codebase Patterns\n     2→- TypeScript source in `src/`, compiled to `lib/` via `tsc`, then bundled to `dist/` via `ncc`\n     3→- Build pipeline: `tsc && ncc build lib/index.js -o dist`\n     4→- `dist/index.js` must be committed (required by GitHub Actions runtime)\n     5→- `lib/` is gitignored (intermediate build output)\n     6→- ESLint configured with `@typescript-eslint/parser` and `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin`\n     7→- Jest configured with `ts-jest` preset, config in `jest.config.js`, tests use `*.test.ts` suffix\n     8→- All stage handlers are in `src/stages/` as default exports\n     9→- Shared types in `src/types.ts` (KilnContext, StageResult, RouteResult, KilnConfig, Octokit)\n    10→- Router returns `RouteResult` with stage name, issueNumber, prNumber, labels, and payload\n    11→- Stage name mapping in index.ts: `re-triage` → triage handler, `release` → ship handler\n    12→- `action.yml` uses `node24` runtime\n    13→- Only `anthropic_api_key` is a required input; others have defaults\n    14→\n    15→## 2026-03-01 - US-001\n    16→- Converted project from JavaScript to TypeScript\n    17→- Set up TypeScript build pipeline: tsc → ncc → dist/\n    18→- Updated action.yml to use node24 and datashaman author\n    19→- Created .eslintrc.json for TypeScript linting\n    20→- Added tsconfig.json with strict mode\n    21→- Files changed:\n    22→  - action.yml (node20 → node24, author fix)\n    23→  - package.json (TypeScript deps, build scripts, lint script)\n    24→  - tsconfig.json (new)\n    25→  - .eslintrc.json (new)\n    26→  - .gitignore (added /lib/, removed /dist/)\n    27→  - src/types.ts (new - shared type definitions)\n    28→  - src/index.ts (converted from .js)\n    29→  - src/router.ts (converted from .js)\n    30→  - src/config.ts (converted from .js)\n    31→  - src/labels.ts (converted from .js)\n    32→  - src/claude.ts (converted from .js)\n    33→  - src/stages/*.ts (all 7 stages converted from .js)\n    34→  - dist/index.js (rebuilt)\n    35→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    36→  - The project uses `@actions/core` and `@actions/github` for GitHub Actions integration\n    37→  - The Octokit type is `InstanceType<typeof GitHub>` from `@actions/github/lib/utils`\n    38→  - Context type is from `@actions/github/lib/context`\n    39→  - `deepMerge` in config.ts needs explicit `unknown` casting to bridge between `KilnConfig` and `Record<string, unknown>`\n    40→  - GitHub Actions requires `dist/` to be committed for the action to work\n    41→---\n    42→\n    43→## 2026-03-01 - US-002\n    44→- Implemented Event Router with full event-to-stage mapping per acceptance criteria\n    45→- Router now returns `RouteResult` object with parsed context (stage, issueNumber, prNumber, labels, payload)\n    46→- Stage names aligned with AC: `re-triage` for issue comments, `release` for approved impl PRs / check_suite\n    47→- Router logs which stage was matched (or \"No matching stage\") via `core.info`\n    48→- Updated `index.ts` STAGES map to route `re-triage` → triage handler and `release` → ship handler\n    49→- Set up Jest testing infrastructure with `ts-jest`\n    50→- Added 21 comprehensive tests covering all event mappings, logging, parsed context, and edge cases\n    51→- Files changed:\n    52→  - src/router.ts (rewritten: returns `RouteResult`, adds logging, stage name changes)\n    53→  - src/types.ts (added `RouteResult` interface)\n    54→  - src/index.ts (updated STAGES map for re-triage/release, handles `RouteResult` return)\n    55→  - src/router.test.ts (new - 21 tests)\n    56→  - jest.config.js (new)\n    57→  - package.json / package-lock.json (added ts-jest, @types/jest)\n    58→  - dist/index.js (rebuilt)\n    59→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    60→  - Jest needs `jest.config.js` (not `.ts`) unless `ts-node` is installed\n    61→  - Mock `@actions/core` with `jest.mock` to test logging calls\n    62→  - Create `makeContext` helper to build minimal `Context` objects for router tests\n    63→  - The router's `extractLabels` helper safely handles missing/undefined label arrays\n    64→---\n    65→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8981eff5-58b5-4df5-8b71-0aaa41565c79","uuid":"ad7e6cd7-6286-400b-92fb-a1f1760e26db","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/marlinf/Projects/datashaman/kiln-action/.chief/prds/main/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- TypeScript source in `src/`, compiled to `lib/` via `tsc`, then bundled to `dist/` via `ncc`\n- Build pipeline: `tsc && ncc build lib/index.js -o dist`\n- `dist/index.js` must be committed (required by GitHub Actions runtime)\n- `lib/` is gitignored (intermediate build output)\n- ESLint configured with `@typescript-eslint/parser` and `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin`\n- Jest configured with `ts-jest` preset, config in `jest.config.js`, tests use `*.test.ts` suffix\n- All stage handlers are in `src/stages/` as default exports\n- Shared types in `src/types.ts` (KilnContext, StageResult, RouteResult, KilnConfig, Octokit)\n- Router returns `RouteResult` with stage name, issueNumber, prNumber, labels, and payload\n- Stage name mapping in index.ts: `re-triage` → triage handler, `release` → ship handler\n- `action.yml` uses `node24` runtime\n- Only `anthropic_api_key` is a required input; others have defaults\n\n## 2026-03-01 - US-001\n- Converted project from JavaScript to TypeScript\n- Set up TypeScript build pipeline: tsc → ncc → dist/\n- Updated action.yml to use node24 and datashaman author\n- Created .eslintrc.json for TypeScript linting\n- Added tsconfig.json with strict mode\n- Files changed:\n  - action.yml (node20 → node24, author fix)\n  - package.json (TypeScript deps, build scripts, lint script)\n  - tsconfig.json (new)\n  - .eslintrc.json (new)\n  - .gitignore (added /lib/, removed /dist/)\n  - 