— Any vulnerabilities? Input validation? Auth checks?\n    50→4. **Performance** — Any N+1 queries, unnecessary loops, memory leaks?\n    51→5. **Error handling** — Are errors caught and handled gracefully?\n    52→6. **Code style** — Does it match existing project conventions?\n    53→7. **Scope** — Are there any changes OUTSIDE the spec's scope?\n    54→\n    55→Respond with a JSON block:\n    56→\\`\\`\\`json\n    57→{\n    58→  \"verdict\": \"approve\" | \"request_changes\",\n    59→  \"summary\": \"Overall assessment in 2-3 sentences\",\n    60→  \"issues\": [\n    61→    {\n    62→      \"file\": \"path/to/file.ts\",\n    63→      \"line\": 42,\n    64→      \"severity\": \"critical\" | \"major\" | \"minor\" | \"nit\",\n    65→      \"comment\": \"Description of the issue and how to fix it\"\n    66→    }\n    67→  ]\n    68→}\n    69→\\`\\`\\`\n    70→\n    71→Be thorough but fair. Only request changes for real issues, not style preferences.`;\n    72→\n    73→  const output = runClaude(prompt, { anthropicKey, timeoutMinutes });\n    74→\n    75→  let reviewResult: {\n    76→    verdict: string;\n    77→    summary: string;\n    78→    issues?: Array<{\n    79→      file: string;\n    80→      line: number;\n    81→      severity: string;\n    82→      comment: string;\n    83→    }>;\n    84→  };\n    85→  try {\n    86→    const jsonMatch =\n    87→      output.match(/```json\\s*([\\s\\S]*?)\\s*```/) ||\n    88→      output.match(/\\{[\\s\\S]*\\}/);\n    89→    const jsonStr = jsonMatch ? jsonMatch[1] || jsonMatch[0] : output;\n    90→    reviewResult = JSON.parse(jsonStr);\n    91→  } catch {\n    92→    core.warning(`Failed to parse review response. Posting raw review.`);\n    93→    await octokit.rest.pulls.createReview({\n    94→      ...context.repo,\n    95→      pull_number: pr.number,\n    96→      body: `🔥 **Kiln Review**\\n\\n${output}`,\n    97→      event: \"COMMENT\",\n    98→    });\n    99→    return { status: \"success\" };\n   100→  }\n   1