{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01C2y5AcLab6uFDLF3F1nnJm","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile the findings.\n\n---\n\nHere is a comprehensive analysis of the `anthropics/claude-code-action` (v1):\n\n## 1. Inputs\n\nThe action accepts the following inputs (from `/action.yml`):\n\n### Core Configuration\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `prompt` | No | `\"\"` | Instructions for Claude. Can be a direct prompt or custom template. |\n| `settings` | No | `\"\"` | Claude Code settings as JSON string or path to settings JSON file |\n| `claude_args` | No | `\"\"` | Additional arguments to pass directly to Claude CLI (e.g., `--max-turns 10 --model claude-4-0-sonnet-20250805 --json-schema '...'`) |\n\n### Trigger Configuration\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `trigger_phrase` | No | `@claude` | Trigger phrase for comments/issues |\n| `assignee_trigger` | No | - | Assignee username trigger |\n| `label_trigger` | No | `claude` | Label trigger |\n\n### Branch Configuration\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `base_branch` | No | - | Base branch for new branches |\n| `branch_prefix` | No | `claude/` | Prefix for Claude branches |\n| `branch_name_template` | No | `\"\"` | Template for branch naming |\n\n### Authentication\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `anthropic_api_key` | No | - | Anthropic API key |\n| `claude_code_oauth_token` | No | - | OAuth token alternative |\n| `github_token` | No | - | GitHub token with repo permissions |\n| `use_bedrock` | No | `false` | Use Amazon Bedrock |\n| `use_vertex` | No | `false` | Use Google Vertex AI |\n| `use_foundry` | No | `false` | Use Microsoft Foundry |\n\n### Behavior Configuration\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `allowed_bots` | No | `\"\"` | Comma-separated bot usernames |\n| `allowed_non_write_users` | No | `\"\"` | Users allowed without write perms |\n| `use_sticky_comment` | No | `false` | Single comment for PR updates |\n| `use_commit_signing` | No | `false` | Enable commit signing |\n| `track_progress` | No | `false` | Force tracking comments |\n| `include_fix_links` | No | `true` | Include 'Fix this' links in reviews |\n| `display_report` | No | `true` | Display report in Step Summary |\n| `show_full_output` | No | `false` | Show full JSON output (security risk) |\n| `plugins` | No | `\"\"` | Newline-separated plugin names |\n| `plugin_marketplaces` | No | `\"\"` | Newline-separated marketplace Git URLs |\n\n### Regarding `direct_prompt`\n\nThe `direct_prompt` input is listed as **DEPRECATED** in the usage docs (`/docs/usage.md`). It existed in v0.x but has been replaced by `prompt` in v1. The migration path is simply: replace `direct_prompt` with `prompt`. The current `action.yml` does **not** declare `direct_prompt` as an input -- it only exists as a deprecated alias mentioned in documentation.\n\n## 2. Outputs\n\nThe action produces these outputs (from `action.yml`):\n\n| Output | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `execution_file` | Path to the Claude Code execution output JSON file |\n| `branch_name` | The branch created by Claude Code for this execution |\n| `github_token` | The GitHub token used by the action (Claude App token if available) |\n| `structured_output` | JSON string containing all structured output fields when `--json-schema` is provided in `claude_args`. Parse with `fromJSON(steps.id.outputs.structured_output).field_name` |\n| `session_id` | The Claude Code session ID that can be used with `--resume` to continue the conversation |\n\n## 3. How It Is Invoked\n\nThe action is a **composite action** (`runs: using: \"composite\"`). This is critical to understand:\n\n**It is designed to be used as a step in a GitHub Actions workflow YAML**, like:\n\n```yaml\nsteps:\n  - uses: anthropics/claude-code-action@v1\n    with:\n      prompt: \"Review this PR for security issues\"\n      anthropic_api_key: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n```\n\n### Internal Architecture\n\nThe composite action's `runs` section:\n1. Installs Bun (via `oven-sh/setup-bun`)\n2. Runs `bun install --production` in the action's directory\n3. Executes `bun run ${GITHUB_ACTION_PATH}/src/entrypoints/run.ts` with environment variables set from all inputs\n4. Cleans up (SSH keys, app tokens)\n\nThe entrypoint (`src/entrypoints/run.ts`) does extensive GitHub context parsing, mode detection (tag vs. agent mode), permission checking, trigger validation, prompt preparation, and then ultimately calls `runClaude()` from `base-action/src/run-claude.ts`.\n\n### The Actual Claude Invocation\n\nAt the deepest level, in `base-action/src/run-claude-sdk.ts`, Claude is invoked using the **`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`** package:\n\n```typescript\nimport { query } from \"@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk\";\n\n// ...\nfor await (const message of query({ prompt, options: sdkOptions })) {\n  // processes streaming messages\n}\n```\n\nThe `query()` function from `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` is the actual programmatic interface. It takes a prompt (string or async iterable of `SDKUserMessage`) and `Options` (model, maxTurns, allowedTools, disallowedTools, systemPrompt, extraArgs, env, etc.) and returns an async iterable of `SDKMessage` objects.\n\n## 4. Can It Be Invoked Programmatically from TypeScript?\n\n**The action itself (`anthropics/claude-code-action@v1`) CANNOT be invoked programmatically from TypeScript code at runtime.** It is a GitHub Actions composite action -- it is meant to be declared as a `uses:` step in a workflow YAML. There is no API to call a composite action from within another action's TypeScript code.\n\n### What You Should Use Instead: `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`\n\nThe real programmatic interface is the **`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`** npm package (currently at v0.2.63). This is what `claude-code-action` itself uses internally. The key export is:\n\n```typescript\nimport { query } from \"@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk\";\nimport type { Options, SDKMessage, SDKResultMessage } from \"@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk\";\n\nconst options: Options = {\n  model: \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\",\n  maxTurns: 10,\n  allowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Read\", \"Write\", \"Bash\"],\n  systemPrompt: \"You are a helpful assistant.\",\n  env: { ...process.env, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: \"...\" },\n};\n\nfor await (const message of query({ prompt: \"Your prompt here\", options })) {\n  if (message.type === \"result\") {\n    const result = message as SDKResultMessage;\n    console.log(result.subtype); // \"success\" or \"failure\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis SDK bundles the Claude Code CLI internally (notice the 80MB package includes `cli.js`, ripgrep binaries, tree-sitter wasm files, etc.). It provides full access to Claude Code's capabilities (file editing, bash execution, tool use) without needing the CLI installed separately.\n\n### Comparison: Your Current Approach vs. Recommended Approach\n\n| Approach | How it works | Pros | Cons |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **`execSync(\"claude ...\")`** (your current) | Shells out to Claude CLI | Simple, works | Requires CLI installed, no streaming, harder to parse output, process management issues |\n| **`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`** (recommended) | Native TypeScript SDK | Streaming messages, typed interfaces, structured output support, same thing `claude-code-action` uses internally | Large package (~80MB), requires Bun or Node 18+ |\n| **`anthropics/claude-code-action@v1`** (not viable) | Composite GitHub Action | Full GitHub integration | Cannot be called from TypeScript; only usable as a workflow step |\n\n### Recommendation for kiln-action\n\nSince your kiln-action needs to invoke Claude from within TypeScript code at runtime, you should use `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` directly. This gives you the same capabilities that `claude-code-action` has, with proper TypeScript types and streaming support. The SDK's `query()` function is the programmatic equivalent of running the `claude` CLI.\n\nThe key files demonstrating the SDK usage pattern are:\n- `base-action/src/run-claude-sdk.ts` -- shows the full `query()` invocation pattern with message handling\n- `base-action/src/parse-sdk-options.ts` -- shows how to construct the `Options` object\n- `base-action/src/run-claude.ts` -- shows the clean wrapper interface"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1f3102 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46150\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 138199</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cab57a4f-e8df-4648-9c51-7e23a35b2ad7","uuid":"2f26cd53-3134-45be-853f-a7820796211d","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Research the `anthropics/claude-code-action` GitHub Action (v1). I need to understand:\n\n1. What inputs does it accept? Specifically: does it support a `direct_prompt` input?\n2. What outputs does it produce?\n3. How is it typically invoked - as a step in a workflow, or can it be called programmatically from within another action's code?\n4. Does it support being used as a \"composite\" action that can be invoked from TypeScript code?\n\nSearch the GitHub repository at https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code-action for its action.yml, README, and any documentation about its inputs/outputs.\n\nImportant context: I'm building a GitHub Action (kiln-action) that needs to invoke claude-code-action from within its TypeScript code at runtime. The current approach uses `execSync` to call a `claude` CLI. I need to understand if claude-code-action can be invoked programmatically or if I need a different approach.\n\nReturn the full details of what you find - inputs, outputs, and how it's meant to be used.","agentId":"a1f3102","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile the findings.\n\n---\n\nHere is a comprehensive analysis of the `anthropics/claude-code-action` (v1):\n\n## 1. Inputs\n\nThe action accepts the following inputs (from `/action.yml`):\n\n### Core Configuration\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `prompt` | No | `\"\"` | Instructions for Claude. Can be a direct prompt or custom template. |\n| `settings` | No | `\"\"` | Claude Code settings as JSON string or path to settings JSON file |\n| `claude_args` | No | `\"\"` | Additional arguments to pass directly to Claude CLI (e.g., `--max-turns 10 --model claude-4-0-sonnet-20250805 --json-schema '...'`) |\n\n### Trigger Configuration\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `trigger_phrase` | No | `@claude` | Trigger phrase for comments/issues |\n| `assignee_trigger` | No | - | Assignee username trigger |\n| `label_trigger` | No | `claude` | Label trigger |\n\n### Branch Configuration\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `base_branch` | No | - | Base branch for new branches |\n| `branch_prefix` | No | `claude/` | Prefix for Claude branches |\n| `branch_name_template` | No | `\"\"` | Template for branch naming |\n\n### Authentication\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `anthropic_api_key` | No | - | Anthropic API key |\n| `claude_code_oauth_token` | No | - | OAuth token alternative |\n| `github_token` | No | - | GitHub token with repo permissions |\n| `use_bedrock` | No | `false` | Use Amazon Bedrock |\n| `use_vertex` | No | `false` | Use Google Vertex AI |\n| `use_foundry` | No | `false` | Use Microsoft Foundry |\n\n### Behavior Configuration\n| Input | Required | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `allowed_bots` | No | `\"\"` | Comma-separated bot usernames |\n| `allowed_non_write_users` | No | `\"\"` | Users allowed without write perms |\n| `use_sticky_comment` | No | `false` | Single comment for PR updates |\n| `use_commit_signing` | No | `false` | Enable commit signing |\n| `track_progress` | No | `false` | Force tracking comments |\n| `include_fix_links` | No | `true` | Include 'Fix this' links in reviews |\n| `display_report` | No | `true` | Display report in Step Summary |\n| `show_full_output` | No | `false` | Show full JSON output (security risk) |\n| `plugins` | No | `\"\"` | Newline-separated plugin names |\n| `plugin_marketplaces` | No | `\"\"` | Newline-separated marketplace Git URLs |\n\n### Regarding `direct_prompt`\n\nThe `direct_prompt` input is listed as **DEPRECATED** in the usage docs (`/docs/usage.md`). It existed in v0.x but has been replaced by `prompt` in v1. The migration path is simply: replace `direct_prompt` with `prompt`. The current `action.yml` does **not** declare `direct_prompt` as an input -- it only exists as a deprecated alias mentioned in documentation.\n\n## 2. Outputs\n\nThe action produces these outputs (from `action.yml`):\n\n| Output | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `execution_file` | Path to the Claude Code execution output JSON file |\n| `branch_name` | The branch created by Claude Code for this execution |\n| `github_token` | The GitHub token used by the action (Claude App token if available) |\n| `structured_output` | JSON string containing all structured output fields when `--json-schema` is provided in `claude_args`. Parse with `fromJSON(steps.id.outputs.structured_output).field_name` |\n| `session_id` | The Claude Code session ID that can be used with `--resume` to continue the conversation |\n\n## 3. How It Is Invoked\n\nThe action is a **composite action** (`runs: using: \"composite\"`). This is critical to understand:\n\n**It is designed to be used as a step in a GitHub Actions workflow YAML**, like:\n\n```yaml\nsteps:\n  - uses: anthropics/claude-code-action@v1\n    with:\n      prompt: \"Review this PR for security issues\"\n      anthropic_api_key: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n```\n\n### Internal Architecture\n\nThe composite action's `runs` section:\n1. Installs Bun (via `oven-sh/setup-bun`)\n2. Runs `bun install --production` in the action's directory\n3. Executes `bun run ${GITHUB_ACTION_PATH}/src/entrypoints/run.ts` with environment variables set from all inputs\n4. Cleans up (SSH keys, app tokens)\n\nThe entrypoint (`src/entrypoints/run.ts`) does extensive GitHub context parsing, mode detection (tag vs. agent mode), permission checking, trigger validation, prompt preparation, and then ultimately calls `runClaude()` from `base-action/src/run-claude.ts`.\n\n### The Actual Claude Invocation\n\nAt the deepest level, in `base-action/src/run-claude-sdk.ts`, Claude is invoked using the **`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`** package:\n\n```typescript\nimport { query } from \"@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk\";\n\n// ...\nfor await (const message of query({ prompt, options: sdkOptions })) {\n  // processes streaming messages\n}\n```\n\nThe `query()` function from `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` is the actual programmatic interface. It takes a prompt (string or async iterable of `SDKUserMessage`) and `Options` (model, maxTurns, allowedTools, disallowedTools, systemPrompt, extraArgs, env, etc.) and returns an async iterable of `SDKMessage` objects.\n\n## 4. Can It Be Invoked Programmatically from TypeScript?\n\n**The action itself (`anthropics/claude-code-action@v1`) CANNOT be invoked programmatically from TypeScript code at runtime.** It is a GitHub Actions composite action -- it is meant to be declared as a `uses:` step in a workflow YAML. There is no API to call a composite action from within another action's TypeScript code.\n\n### What You Should Use Instead: `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`\n\nThe real programmatic interface is the **`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`** npm package (currently at v0.2.63). This is what `claude-code-action` itself uses internally. The key export is:\n\n```typescript\nimport { query } from \"@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk\";\nimport type { Options, SDKMessage, SDKResultMessage } from \"@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk\";\n\nconst options: Options = {\n  model: \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\",\n  maxTurns: 10,\n  allowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Read\", \"Write\", \"Bash\"],\n  systemPrompt: \"You are a helpful assistant.\",\n  env: { ...process.env, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: \"...\" },\n};\n\nfor await (const message of query({ prompt: \"Your prompt here\", options })) {\n  if (message.type === \"result\") {\n    const result = message as SDKResultMessage;\n    console.log(result.subtype); // \"success\" or \"failure\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis SDK bundles the Claude Code CLI internally (notice the 80MB package includes `cli.js`, ripgrep binaries, tree-sitter wasm files, etc.). It provides full access to Claude Code's capabilities (file editing, bash execution, tool use) without needing the CLI installed separately.\n\n### Comparison: Your Current Approach vs. Recommended Approach\n\n| Approach | How it works | Pros | Cons |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **`execSync(\"claude ...\")`** (your current) | Shells out to Claude CLI | Simple, works | Requires CLI installed, no streaming, harder to parse output, process management issues |\n| **`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`** (recommended) | Native TypeScript SDK | Streaming messages, typed interfaces, structured output support, same thing `claude-code-action` uses internally | Large package (~80MB), requires Bun or Node 18+ |\n| **`anthropics/claude-code-action@v1`** (not viable) | Composite GitHub Action | Full GitHub integration | Cannot be called from TypeScript; only usable as a workflow step |\n\n### Recommendation for kiln-action\n\nSince your kiln-action needs to invoke Claude from within TypeScript code at runtime, you should use `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` directly. This gives you the same capabilities that `claude-code-action` has, with proper TypeScript types and streaming support. The SDK's `query()` function is the programmatic equivalent of running the `claude` CLI.\n\nThe key files demonstrating the SDK usage pattern are:\n- `base-action/src/run-claude-sdk.ts` -- shows the full `query()` invocation pattern with message handling\n- `base-action/src/parse-sdk-options.ts` -- shows how to construct the `Options` object\n- `base-action/src/run-claude.ts` -- shows the clean wrapper interface"}],"totalDurationMs":138199,"totalTokens":46150,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":630,"cache_read_input_tokens":43205,"output_tokens":2314,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":630,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
