{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WeLXJLhNSHjhjrrh4fvpwU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` is 80MB and bundles the entire CLI. Given the AC says \"shells out to / invokes anthropics/claude-code-action@v1\", and looking at how this project is structured (the existing `claude.ts` already uses `execSync` to shell out to the `claude` CLI), the most practical approach is:\n\n1. Keep the existing CLI-based approach (using `@anthropic-ai/claude-code` which provides the `claude` binary)\n2. Refactor `claude.ts` into a proper integration layer that meets all AC requirements: error handling with issue/PR comments, timeouts, secure API key handling, and consistent interface\n\nThe `claude-code-action` itself invokes the CLI at its core. The key improvement is creating a clean utility with proper error surfacing and security. Let me remove the 80MB SDK and work with what we have."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":811,"cache_read_input_tokens":50633,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":811},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cab57a4f-e8df-4648-9c51-7e23a35b2ad7","uuid":"c06e1c1e-f890-4faf-807b-3eb8f0479852"}
