{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017okBp7cKgXMTb25AhyT7ae","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Codebase Patterns\n     2→- TypeScript source in `src/`, compiled to `lib/` via `tsc`, then bundled to `dist/` via `ncc`\n     3→- Build pipeline: `tsc && ncc build lib/index.js -o dist`\n     4→- `dist/index.js` must be committed (required by GitHub Actions runtime)\n     5→- `lib/` is gitignored (intermediate build output)\n     6→- ESLint configured with `@typescript-eslint/parser` and `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin`\n     7→- Jest configured with `ts-jest` preset, config in `jest.config.js`, tests use `*.test.ts` suffix\n     8→- All stage handlers are in `src/stages/` as default exports\n     9→- Shared types in `src/types.ts` (KilnContext, StageResult, RouteResult, KilnConfig, Octokit)\n    10→- Router returns `RouteResult` with stage name, issueNumber, prNumber, labels, and payload\n    11→- Stage name mapping in index.ts: `re-triage` → triage handler, `release` → ship handler\n    12→- `action.yml` uses `node24` runtime\n    13→- Only `anthropic_api_key` is a required input; others have defaults\n    14→- Blocked guard in `src/blocked.ts` runs before stage detection; checks `{prefix}:blocked` label on issues and PRs\n    15→- For PR events, blocked guard checks both PR labels and linked issue labels (via `Closes #N` in PR body)\n    16→- Claude integration layer in `src/claude.ts` exports `invokeClaude` (async, returns `ClaudeResult`), `runClaude` (sync, read-only), `runClaudeEdit` (sync, edit mode)\n    17→- `invokeClaude` accepts `ClaudeConfig` with optional octokit/context for error comment surfacing\n    18→- Error comments are branded and API keys are redacted from any output\n    19→\n    20→## 2026-03-01 - US-001\n    21→- Converted project from JavaScript to TypeScript\n    22→- Set up TypeScript build pipeline: tsc → ncc → dist/\n    23→- Updated action.yml to use node24 and datashaman author\n    24→- Created .eslintrc.json for TypeScript linting\n    25→- Added tsconfig.json with strict mode\n    26→- Files changed:\n    27→  - action.yml (node20 → node24, author fix)\n    28→  - package.json (TypeScript deps, build scripts, lint script)\n    29→  - tsconfig.json (new)\n    30→  - .eslintrc.json (new)\n    31→  - .gitignore (added /lib/, removed /dist/)\n    32→  - src/types.ts (new - shared type definitions)\n    33→  - src/index.ts (converted from .js)\n    34→  - src/router.ts (converted from .js)\n    35→  - src/config.ts (converted from .js)\n    36→  - src/labels.ts (converted from .js)\n    37→  - src/claude.ts (converted from .js)\n    38→  - src/stages/*.ts (all 7 stages converted from .js)\n    39→  - dist/index.js (rebuilt)\n    40→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    41→  - The project uses `@actions/core` and `@actions/github` for GitHub Actions integration\n    42→  - The Octokit type is `InstanceType<typeof GitHub>` from `@actions/github/lib/utils`\n    43→  - Context type is from `@actions/github/lib/context`\n    44→  - `deepMerge` in config.ts needs explicit `unknown` casting to bridge between `KilnConfig` and `Record<string, unknown>`\n    45→  - GitHub Actions requires `dist/` to be committed for the action to work\n    46→---\n    47→\n    48→## 2026-03-01 - US-002\n    49→- Implemented Event Router with full event-to-stage mapping per acceptance criteria\n    50→- Router now returns `RouteResult` object with parsed context (stage, issueNumber, prNumber, labels, payload)\n    51→- Stage names aligned with AC: `re-triage` for issue comments, `release` for approved impl PRs / check_suite\n    52→- Router logs which stage was matched (or \"No matching stage\") via `core.info`\n    53→- Updated `index.ts` STAGES map to route `re-triage` → triage handler and `release` → ship handler\n    54→- Set up Jest testing infrastructure with `ts-jest`\n    55→- Added 21 comprehensive tests covering all event mappings, logging, parsed context, and edge cases\n    56→- Files changed:\n    57→  - src/router.ts (rewritten: returns `RouteResult`, adds logging, stage name changes)\n    58→  - src/types.ts (added `RouteResult` interface)\n    59→  - src/index.ts (updated STAGES map for re-triage/release, handles `RouteResult` return)\n    60→  - src/router.test.ts (new - 21 tests)\n    61→  - jest.config.js (new)\n    62→  - package.json / package-lock.json (added ts-jest, @types/jest)\n    63→  - dist/index.js (rebuilt)\n    64→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    65→  - Jest needs `jest.config.js` (not `.ts`) unless `ts-node` is installed\n    66→  - Mock `@actions/core` with `jest.mock` to test logging calls\n    67→  - Create `makeContext` helper to build minimal `Context` objects for router tests\n    68→  - The router's `extractLabels` helper safely handles missing/undefined label arrays\n    69→---\n    70→\n    71→## 2026-03-01 - US-003\n    72→- Extracted blocked guard into dedicated `src/blocked.ts` module (was inline in index.ts)\n    73→- `checkBlocked` checks issue labels (from payload) for `kiln:blocked` label\n    74→- For PR events, checks both PR labels AND linked issue labels (via `Closes #N` in PR body)\n    75→- Posts branded comment when blocked: \"🔥 **Kiln** — Automation is blocked on this item. Remove kiln:blocked to resume.\"\n    76→- Exits cleanly (exit code 0) without running the stage when blocked\n    77→- Supports custom label prefix from config\n    78→- Comment posting is best-effort (catches errors to avoid failing the guard)\n    79→- Files changed:\n    80→  - src/blocked.ts (new - extracted blocked guard logic)\n    81→  - src/blocked.test.ts (new - 26 tests covering all AC)\n    82→  - src/index.ts (imports `checkBlocked` from blocked.ts, removed inline `isBlocked`)\n    83→  - dist/index.js (rebuilt)\n    84→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    85→  - Extract testable logic into separate modules rather than keeping it inline in index.ts\n    86→  - Mock Octokit with `jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({})` for issues.createComment and issues.get\n    87→  - Use `as unknown as jest.Mock` when casting Octokit methods that TypeScript can't bridge to Mock type\n    88→  - PR body parsing uses `Closes #(\\d+)` (case-insensitive) to find linked issue number\n    89→  - The blocked guard runs before stage detection in the pipeline — it's a pre-router check\n    90→---\n    91→\n    92→## 2026-03-01 - US-004\n    93→- Refactored `src/claude.ts` into a proper integration layer for Claude Code\n    94→- Added `invokeClaude()` — the primary async utility function that returns `ClaudeResult` with structured success/error handling\n    95→- `ClaudeConfig` interface accepts: prompt, anthropicKey, timeoutMinutes, allowEdits, octokit, context\n    96→- Kept backward-compatible `runClaude()` and `runClaudeEdit()` wrappers used by existing stages\n    97→- Timeout handling: defaults to 30 minutes (matching claude-code-action v1), detects killed processes for specific timeout messages\n    98→- Error surfacing: posts branded \"🔥 **Kiln** — Claude Code error:\" comments on issues/PRs when octokit+context provided\n    99→- API key security: passed only via `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` env var (never in command string), redacted from error comments\n   100→- Added `sanitizeOutput()` to strip API keys from any error messages before posting\n   101→- Added `resolveCommentTarget()` to find the right issue/PR number from context payload\n   102→- Comment posting is best-effort (catches failures)\n   103→- Files changed:\n   104→  - src/claude.ts (refactored - added invokeClaude, ClaudeConfig, ClaudeResult, error surfacing, API key redaction)\n   105→  - src/claude.test.ts (new - 29 tests covering all AC)\n   106→  - dist/index.js (rebuilt)\n   107→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n   108→  - `anthropics/claude-code-action@v1` is a composite GitHub Action that cannot be invoked programmatically from TypeScript — it's only usable as a `uses:` step in workflow YAML\n   109→  - The underlying SDK is `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` (80MB, bundles entire CLI)\n   110→  - For this project, shelling out to the `claude` CLI via `execSync` is the pragmatic approach (same as what claude-code-action does internally)\n   111→  - Detect timeout via `error.killed` property on the error thrown by `execSync`\n   112→  - Use `escapeRegExp()` when building regex from user-controlled strings (API key) to avoid regex injection\n   113→  - `process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in tests needs explicit cleanup in `beforeEach` to avoid test pollution\n   114→---\n   115→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f20d6a69-1eae-4f47-9a8a-63b220fe9642","uuid":"6e7a363c-f9c1-4c58-aba8-34c3da2509e1","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/marlinf/Projects/datashaman/kiln-action/.chief/prds/main/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- TypeScript source in `src/`, compiled to `lib/` via `tsc`, then bundled to `dist/` via `ncc`\n- Build pipeline: `tsc && ncc build lib/index.js -o dist`\n- `dist/index.js` must be committed (required by GitHub Actions runtime)\n- `lib/` is gitignored (intermediate build output)\n- ESLint configured with `@typescript-eslint/parser` and `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin`\n- Jest configured with `ts-jest` preset, config in `jest.config.js`, tests use `*.test.ts` suffix\n- All stage handlers are in `src/stages/` as default exports\n- Shared types in `src/types.ts` (KilnContext, StageResult, RouteResult, KilnConfig, Octokit)\n- Router returns `RouteResult` with stage name, issueNumber, prNumber, labels, and payload\n- Stage name mapping in index.ts: `re-triage` → triage handler, `release` → ship handler\n- `action.yml` uses `node24` runtime\n- Only `anthropic_api_key` is a required input; others have defaults\n- Blocked guard in `src/blocked.ts` runs before stage detection; checks `{prefix}:blocked` label on issues and PRs\n- For PR events, blocked guard checks both PR labels and linked issue labels (via `Closes #N` in PR body)\n- Claude integration layer in `src/claude.ts` exports `invokeClaude` (async, returns `ClaudeResult`), `runClaude` (sync, read-only), `runClaudeEdit` (sync, edit mode)\n- `invokeClaude` accepts `ClaudeConfig` with optional octokit/context for error comment surfacing\n- Error comments are branded and API keys are redacted from any output\n\n## 2026-03-01 - US-001\n- Converted project from JavaScript to TypeScript\n- Set up TypeScript build pipeline: tsc → ncc → dist/\n- Updated action.yml to use node24 and datashaman author\n- Created .eslintrc.json for TypeScript linting\n- Added tsconfig.json with strict mode\n- Files changed:\n  - action.yml (node20 → node24, author fix)\n  - package.json (TypeScript deps, build scripts, lint script)\n  - tsconfig.json (new)\n  - .eslintrc.json (new)\n  - .gitignore (added /lib/, removed /dist/)\n  - src/types.ts (new - shared type definitions)\n  - src/index.ts (converted from .js)\n  - src/router.ts (converted from .js)\n  - src/config.ts (converted from .js)\n  - src/labels.ts (converted from .js)\n  - src/claude.ts (converted from .js)\n  - src/stages/*.ts (all 7 stages converted from .js)\n  - dist/index.js (rebuilt)\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - The project uses `@actions/core` and `@actions/github` for GitHub Actions integration\n  - The Octokit type is `InstanceType<typeof GitHub>` from `@actions/github/lib/utils`\n  - Context type is from `@actions/github/lib/context`\n  - `deepMerge` in config.ts needs explicit `unknown` casting to bridge between `KilnConfig` and `Record<string, unknown>`\n  - GitHub Actions requires `dist/` to be committed for the action to work\n---\n\n## 2026-03-01 - US-002\n- Implemented Event Router with full event-to-stage mapping per acceptance criteria\n- Router now returns `RouteResult` object with parsed context (stage, issueNumber, prNumber, labels, payload)\n- Stage names aligned with AC: `re-triage` for issue comments, `release` for approved impl PRs / check_suite\n- Router logs which stage was matched (or \"No matching stage\") via `core.info`\n- Updated `index.ts` STAGES map to route `re-triage` → triage handler and `release` → ship handler\n- Set up Jest testing infrastructure with `ts-jest`\n- Added 21 comprehensive tests covering all event mappings, logging, parsed context, and edge cases\n- Files changed:\n  - src/router.ts (rewritten: returns `RouteResult`, adds logging, stage name changes)\n  - src/types.ts (added `RouteResult` interface)\n  - src/index.ts (updated STAGES map for re-triage/release, handles `RouteResult` return)\n  - src/router.test.ts (new - 21 tests)\n  - jest.config.js (new)\n  - package.json / package-lock.json (added ts-jest, @types/jest)\n  - dist/index.js (rebuilt)\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - Jest needs `jest.config.js` (not `.ts`) unless `ts-node` is installed\n  - Mock `@actions/core` with `jest.mock` to test logging calls\n  - Create `makeContext` helper to build minimal `Context` objects for router tests\n  - The router's `extractLabels` helper safely handles missing/undefined label arrays\n---\n\n## 2026-03-01 - US-003\n- Extracted blocked guard into dedicated `src/blocked.ts` module (was inline in index.ts)\n- `checkBlocked` checks issue labels (from payload) for `kiln:blocked` label\n- For PR events, checks both PR labels AND linked issue labels (via `Closes #N` in PR body)\n- Posts branded comment when blocked: \"🔥 **Kiln** — Automation is blocked on this item. Remove kiln:blocked to resume.\"\n- Exits cleanly (exit code 0) without running the stage when blocked\n- Supports custom label prefix from config\n- Comment posting is best-effort (catches errors to avoid failing the guard)\n- Files changed:\n  - src/blocked.ts (new - extracted blocked guard logic)\n  - src/blocked.test.ts (new - 26 tests covering all AC)\n  - src/index.ts (imports `checkBlocked` from blocked.ts, removed inline `isBlocked`)\n  - dist/index.js (rebuilt)\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - Extract testable logic into separate modules rather than keeping it inline in index.ts\n  - Mock Octokit with `jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({})` for issues.createComment and issues.get\n  - Use `as unknown as jest.Mock` when casting Octokit methods that TypeScript can't bridge to Mock type\n  - PR body parsing uses `Closes #(\\d+)` (case-insensitive) to find linked issue number\n  - The blocked guard runs before stage detection in the pipeline — it's a pre-router check\n---\n\n## 2026-03-01 - US-004\n- Refactored `src/claude.ts` into a proper integration layer for Claude Code\n- Added `invokeClaude()` — the primary async utility function that returns `ClaudeResult` with structured success/error handling\n- `ClaudeConfig` interface accepts: prompt, anthropicKey, timeoutMinutes, allowEdits, octokit, context\n- Kept backward-compatible `runClaude()` and `runClaudeEdit()` wrappers used by existing stages\n- Timeout handling: defaults to 30 minutes (matching claude-code-action v1), detects killed processes for specific timeout messages\n- Error surfacing: posts branded \"🔥 **Kiln** — Claude Code error:\" comments on issues/PRs when octokit+context provided\n- API key security: passed only via `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` env var (never in command string), redacted from error comments\n- Added `sanitizeOutput()` to strip API keys from any error messages before posting\n- Added `resolveCommentTarget()` to find the right issue/PR number from context payload\n- Comment posting is best-effort (catches failures)\n- Files changed:\n  - src/claude.ts (refactored - added invokeClaude, ClaudeConfig, ClaudeResult, error surfacing, API key redaction)\n  - src/claude.test.ts (new - 29 tests covering all AC)\n  - dist/index.js (rebuilt)\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - `anthropics/claude-code-action@v1` is a composite GitHub Action that cannot be invoked programmatically from TypeScript — it's only usable as a `uses:` step in workflow YAML\n  - The underlying SDK is `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` (80MB, bundles entire CLI)\n  - For this project, shelling out to the `claude` CLI via `execSync` is the pragmatic approach (same as what claude-code-action does internally)\n  - Detect timeout via `error.killed` property on the error thrown by `execSync`\n  - Use `escapeRegExp()` when building regex from user-controlled strings (API key) to avoid regex injection\n  - `process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in tests needs explicit cleanup in `beforeEach` to avoid test pollution\n---\n","numLines":115,"startLine":1,"totalLines":115}}}
