{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ue4nXiGsT1BPytFWCmJjwD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{\n     2→  \"project\": \"Kiln Action\",\n     3→  \"description\": \"Kiln is a single reusable GitHub Action (datashaman/kiln-action@v1) that provides an AI-powered development pipeline. Users file an issue, and Kiln automatically triages it, writes a spec, implements it, reviews it, and ships it — all orchestrated through one action that routes internally based on GitHub event type and label state.\",\n     4→  \"userStories\": [\n     5→    {\n     6→      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n     7→      \"title\": \"Action Entry Point \\u0026 Project Scaffolding\",\n     8→      \"description\": \"As a developer building Kiln, I want the foundational action structure (action.yml, TypeScript build pipeline, dist/ output) so that the action can be installed and invoked in any GitHub repo.\",\n     9→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    10→        \"action.yml exists with runs.using: node24 and runs.main: dist/index.js\",\n    11→        \"Single required input: anthropic_api_key\",\n    12→        \"TypeScript source compiles to dist/ via ncc or equivalent bundler\",\n    13→        \"package.json with build, test, and lint scripts\",\n    14→        \"Action can be referenced as uses: datashaman/kiln-action@v1 in a workflow\",\n    15→        \"Entry point (src/index.ts) reads the GitHub event payload and invokes the router\"\n    16→      ],\n    17→      \"priority\": 1,\n    18→      \"passes\": true\n    19→    },\n    20→    {\n    21→      \"id\": \"US-002\",\n    22→      \"title\": \"Event Router\",\n    23→      \"description\": \"As Kiln, I want to inspect the incoming GitHub event type, action, and label state to determine which pipeline stage to execute, so that one action handles all stages.\",\n    24→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    25→        \"Router maps events to stages per these rules: issues.opened → triage; issue_comment.created (if issue has kiln:intake or kiln:needs-info) → re-triage; issues.labeled with kiln:specifying → specify; pull_request_review.submitted approved on PR with kiln:spec label → approve-spec; issues.labeled with kiln:implementing → implement; pull_request.opened or pull_request.synchronize on PR with kiln:implementation label → review; pull_request_review.submitted with changes_requested on PR with kiln:implementation label → fix; pull_request_review.submitted approved or check_suite.completed on PR with kiln:implementation label → release\",\n    26→        \"Unmatched events result in a clean no-op exit (exit code 0, no error)\",\n    27→        \"Router logs which stage it selected (or \\\"no matching stage\\\") for debugging\",\n    28→        \"Router passes parsed context (issue number, PR number, labels, event payload) to the selected stage handler\"\n    29→      ],\n    30→      \"priority\": 2,\n    31→      \"passes\": true\n    32→    },\n    33→    {\n    34→      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n    35→      \"title\": \"Blocked Guard\",\n    36→      \"description\": \"As a repo maintainer, I want to add kiln:blocked to any issue or PR to immediately halt all Kiln automation on that item, so that I have an emergency stop.\",\n    37→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    38→        \"Before executing any stage, the router checks if the relevant issue or PR has the kiln:blocked label\",\n    39→        \"If blocked, Kiln posts a comment: \\\"🔥 **Kiln** — Automation is blocked on this item. Remove kiln:blocked to resume.\\\"\",\n    40→        \"If blocked, Kiln exits cleanly (exit code 0) without running the stage\",\n    41→        \"The blocked check covers all stages: triage, re-triage, specify, approve-spec, implement, review, fix, release\",\n    42→        \"For PR events, Kiln checks both the PR labels and the linked issue labels for kiln:blocked\"\n    43→      ],\n    44→      \"priority\": 3,\n    45→      \"passes\": true\n    46→    },\n    47→    {\n    48→      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n    49→      \"title\": \"Claude Code Action Integration Layer\",\n    50→      \"description\": \"As Kiln, I want a shared utility to invoke anthropics/claude-code-action@v1 with a prompt and receive structured output, so that all AI stages use a consistent integration pattern.\",\n    51→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    52→        \"Utility function accepts: prompt (string), anthropic API key, and optional configuration\",\n    53→        \"Utility shells out to / invokes anthropics/claude-code-action@v1 passing the prompt via direct_prompt\",\n    54→        \"Utility captures and returns the action's output\",\n    55→        \"Utility handles timeouts (hard-coded 30 minutes default in v1)\",\n    56→        \"Utility handles errors and surfaces them as issue/PR comments when possible\",\n    57→        \"API key is passed securely (never logged or exposed in comments)\"\n    58→      ],\n    59→      \"priority\": 4,\n    60→      \"passes\": true,\n    61→      \"inProgress\": false\n    62→    },\n    63→    {\n    64→      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n    65→      \"title\": \"Stage 1 — Triage (Issue Opened)\",\n    66→      \"description\": \"As a repo maintainer, I want new issues to be automatically classified by type, complexity, and clarity so that the pipeline can proceed or request more information.\",\n    67→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    68→        \"Triggers on issues.opened\",\n    69→        \"Sends issue title and body to Claude with a triage prompt\",\n    70→        \"Claude responds with structured JSON: { type, complexity, clear_enough, comment, labels }\",\n    71→        \"Kiln parses the JSON response and applies labels: type:{type}, size:{complexity}\",\n    72→        \"If clear_enough is true: applies kiln:specifying label, posts confirmation comment\",\n    73→        \"If clear_enough is false: applies kiln:needs-info label, posts clarification comment from Claude\",\n    74→        \"Posts a Kiln-branded comment indicating triage result\"\n    75→      ],\n    76→      \"priority\": 5,\n    77→      \"passes\": true,\n    78→      \"inProgress\": false\n    79→    },\n    80→    {\n    81→      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n    82→      \"title\": \"Stage 1b — Re-triage (Issue Comment After Clarification)\",\n    83→      \"description\": \"As an issue author, I want Kiln to re-evaluate my issue after I provide clarification so that the pipeline can proceed.\",\n    84→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    85→        \"Triggers on issue_comment.created\",\n    86→        \"Only runs if the issue has kiln:intake or kiln:needs-info label\",\n    87→        \"Ignores comments from bots/actions (prevents infinite loops)\",\n    88→        \"Sends full issue body + all comments to Claude for re-triage\",\n    89→        \"If now clear enough: removes kiln:needs-info, applies kiln:specifying, posts confirmation\",\n    90→        \"If still unclear: posts follow-up clarification request, keeps kiln:needs-info\"\n    91→      ],\n    92→      \"priority\": 6,\n    93→      \"passes\": true,\n    94→      \"inProgress\": false\n    95→    },\n    96→    {\n    97→      \"id\": \"US-007\",\n    98→      \"title\": \"Stage 2 — Specification Agent\",\n    99→      \"description\": \"As Kiln, I want to generate a detailed implementation spec from a triaged issue so that the implementation agent has clear instructions.\",\n   100→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   101→        \"Triggers when issue receives kiln:specifying label\",\n   102→        \"Checks out the repo and sends issue context + codebase access to Claude\",\n   103→        \"Claude creates a spec file at specs/issue-{number}.md with sections: Overview, Requirements, Technical Design, Test Plan, Out of Scope, Implementation Notes\",\n   104→        \"Claude commits the spec to branch kiln/spec/issue-{number} and pushes\",\n   105→        \"Kiln opens a PR titled \\\"📋 Kiln Spec: {issue title}\\\" targeting main\",\n   106→        \"PR body references the issue number and includes review instructions\",\n   107→        \"PR is labeled with kiln:spec and needs-human-review\",\n   108→        \"Issue is updated: kiln:specifying removed, kiln:spec-review added\",\n   109→        \"Comment posted on issue linking to the spec PR\"\n   110→      ],\n   111→      \"priority\": 7,\n   112→      \"passes\": false\n   113→    },\n   114→    {\n   115→      \"id\": \"US-008\",\n   116→      \"title\": \"Stage 3 — Human Spec Approval Gate\",\n   117→      \"description\": \"As a repo maintainer, I want spec PRs to require my explicit approval before implementation begins, so that I control what gets built.\",\n   118→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   119→        \"Triggers on pull_request_review.submitted where state is approved\",\n   120→        \"Only runs on PRs with the kiln:spec label\",\n   121→        \"Merges the spec PR via squash merge\",\n   122→        \"Extracts the issue number from the branch name (kiln/spec/issue-{number})\",\n   123→        \"Applies kiln:implementing label to the linked issue\",\n   124→        \"Removes kiln:spec-review label from the issue\",\n   125→        \"Posts comment on the issue: implementation agent is starting\"\n   126→      ],\n   127→      \"priority\": 8,\n   128→      \"passes\": false\n   129→    },\n   130→    {\n   131→      \"id\": \"US-009\",\n   132→      \"title\": \"Stage 4 — Implementation Agent\",\n   133→      \"description\": \"As Kiln, I want to generate a full implementation (code + tests) from an approved spec so that the feature is built automatically.\",\n   134→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   135→        \"Triggers when issue receives kiln:implementing label\",\n   136→        \"Checks out the repo and reads the spec at specs/issue-{number}.md\",\n   137→        \"Sends spec + codebase context to Claude with implementation prompt\",\n   138→        \"Claude implements on branch kiln/impl/issue-{number}, following project conventions from CLAUDE.md\",\n   139→        \"Claude writes all tests specified in the Test Plan\",\n   140→        \"Claude runs tests and lint, fixing failures before committing\",\n   141→        \"Uses conventional commits (feat:, fix:, chore:, etc.)\",\n   142→        \"Kiln opens a PR titled \\\"🔨 Kiln Impl: {issue title}\\\" targeting main\",\n   143→        \"PR body references spec file and includes Closes #{issue_number}\",\n   144→        \"PR is labeled with kiln:implementation and needs-review\",\n   145→        \"Issue is updated: kiln:implementing removed, kiln:in-review added\",\n   146→        \"Comment posted on issue linking to the implementation PR\"\n   147→      ],\n   148→      \"priority\": 9,\n   149→      \"passes\": false\n   150→    },\n   151→    {\n   152→      \"id\": \"US-010\",\n   153→      \"title\": \"Stage 5 — AI Code Review\",\n   154→      \"description\": \"As Kiln, I want implementation PRs to be automatically reviewed by an AI reviewer so that code quality is validated before merge.\",\n   155→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   156→        \"Triggers on pull_request.opened and pull_request.synchronize\",\n   157→        \"Only runs on PRs with the kiln:implementation label\",\n   158→        \"Checks out the repo with full history (fetch-depth: 0)\",\n   159→        \"Claude reads the referenced spec and reviews the diff against acceptance criteria\",\n   160→        \"Review covers: correctness, security, performance, error handling, test coverage, style consistency\",\n   161→        \"If everything passes: Claude approves the PR\",\n   162→        \"If issues found: Claude requests changes with specific inline comments and fix instructions\",\n   163→        \"Review is posted as a proper GitHub PR review (not just comments)\"\n   164→      ],\n   165→      \"priority\": 10,\n   166→      \"passes\": false\n   167→    },\n   168→    {\n   169→      \"id\": \"US-011\",\n   170→      \"title\": \"Stage 6 — Fix Review Feedback\",\n   171→      \"description\": \"As Kiln, I want the implementation agent to automatically address review feedback so that the PR can be re-reviewed and approved.\",\n   172→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   173→        \"Triggers on pull_request_review.submitted where state is changes_requested\",\n   174→        \"Only runs on PRs with the kiln:implementation label\",\n   175→        \"Checks out the PR's head branch\",\n   176→        \"Claude reads all review comments and inline feedback\",\n   177→        \"Claude addresses each comment: fixes code, adds tests, resolves concerns\",\n   178→        \"Claude commits fixes and pushes to the PR branch\",\n   179→        \"Claude replies to each review comment explaining the changes made\",\n   180→        \"The push triggers a new synchronize event, which triggers re-review (Stage 5)\"\n   181→      ],\n   182→      \"priority\": 11,\n   183→      \"passes\": false\n   184→    },\n   185→    {\n   186→      \"id\": \"US-012\",\n   187→      \"title\": \"Stage 7 — Auto-merge \\u0026 Release\",\n   188→      \"description\": \"As Kiln, I want approved implementation PRs with green CI to be automatically merged and released so that the pipeline completes without manual intervention.\",\n   189→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   190→        \"Triggers on pull_request_review.submitted (approved) and check_suite.completed\",\n   191→        \"Only runs on PRs with the kiln:implementation label\",\n   192→        \"Checks that the PR has at least one approval\",\n   193→        \"Checks that all CI checks are passing (success or skipped)\",\n   194→        \"If both conditions met: merges the PR via squash merge\",\n   195→        \"Extracts issue number from PR body (Closes #N)\",\n   196→        \"Applies kiln:done label to the issue\",\n   197→        \"Closes the issue\",\n   198→        \"Posts a final Kiln comment on the issue confirming release\",\n   199→        \"If conditions not met: no-op (waits for remaining condition)\"\n   200→      ],\n   201→      \"priority\": 12,\n   202→      \"passes\": false\n   203→    },\n   204→    {\n   205→      \"id\": \"US-013\",\n   206→      \"title\": \"Label Definitions \\u0026 Setup Documentation\",\n   207→      \"description\": \"As a user installing Kiln, I want clear documentation of the required labels and their hex colors so that I can set up my repo correctly.\",\n   208→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   209→        \"README documents all required labels with names, descriptions, and hex colors: Pipeline state (kiln:intake, kiln:needs-info, kiln:specifying, kiln:spec-review, kiln:implementing, kiln:in-review, kiln:done, kiln:blocked), PR markers (kiln:spec, kiln:implementation, needs-human-review, needs-review), Type (type:feature, type:bug, type:improvement, type:chore), Size (size:xs, size:s, size:m, size:l, size:xl)\",\n   210→        \"A setup script or GitHub Actions workflow is provided (or documented steps) to create all labels\"\n   211→      ],\n   212→      \"priority\": 13,\n   213→      \"passes\": false\n   214→    },\n   215→    {\n   216→      \"id\": \"US-014\",\n   217→      \"title\": \"Loop Prevention \\u0026 Edge Case Handling\",\n   218→      \"description\": \"As Kiln, I want safeguards against infinite loops and race conditions so that the pipeline doesn't run away or corrupt state.\",\n   219→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   220→        \"Bot/action comments are ignored in re-triage (prevents triage → comment → re-triage loop)\",\n   221→        \"Label events triggered by Kiln itself don't cause duplicate stage runs (debounce or actor check)\",\n   222→        \"If a stage fails, Kiln posts an error comment on the issue/PR and does not advance the pipeline\",\n   223→        \"If a spec PR already exists for an issue, the specify stage does not create a duplicate\",\n   224→        \"If an implementation PR already exists for an issue, the implement stage does not create a duplicate\",\n   225→        \"Concurrent events for the same issue are handled gracefully (last-write-wins or queue)\"\n   226→      ],\n   227→      \"priority\": 14,\n   228→      \"passes\": false\n   229→    },\n   230→    {\n   231→      \"id\": \"US-015\",\n   232→      \"title\": \"Error Handling \\u0026 Observability\",\n   233→      \"description\": \"As a repo maintainer, I want clear error reporting and logging so that I can diagnose pipeline failures.\",\n   234→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   235→        \"All stages wrap execution in try/catch and post error details as issue/PR comments\",\n   236→        \"Error comments are clearly branded (e.g. \\\"🔥 **Kiln** — Error in {stage}: {message}\\\")\",\n   237→        \"GitHub Actions step outputs include the stage name, duration, and result\",\n   238→        \"Failed stages do not advance the pipeline (no label changes on error)\",\n   239→        \"Timeout errors produce a specific message indicating the stage timed out\"\n   240→      ],\n   241→      \"priority\": 15,\n   242→      \"passes\": false\n   243→    },\n   244→    {\n   245→      \"id\": \"US-016\",\n   246→      \"title\": \"README \\u0026 Getting Started Guide\",\n   247→      \"description\": \"As a developer who wants to use Kiln, I want a clear README with install instructions and a usage guide so that I can set up the pipeline in my repo.\",\n   248→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   249→        \"README includes: project overview, pipeline diagram, install steps, configuration reference\",\n   250→        \"Install steps cover: adding ANTHROPIC_API_KEY secret, creating labels, adding workflow file, adding CLAUDE.md\",\n   251→        \"Example workflow file is provided (copy-paste ready)\",\n   252→        \"Example CLAUDE.md template is provided with placeholder sections\",\n   253→        \"Safety controls documented: kiln:blocked label, branch protections, timeouts\",\n   254→        \"Troubleshooting section covers common issues (missing labels, missing secret, permissions)\"\n   255→      ],\n   256→      \"priority\": 16,\n   257→      \"passes\": false\n   258→    },\n   259→    {\n   260→      \"id\": \"US-017\",\n   261→      \"title\": \"Example Workflow File\",\n   262→      \"description\": \"As a user installing Kiln, I want a ready-to-use workflow file so that I can copy it into my repo and start using Kiln immediately.\",\n   263→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   264→        \"Example file provided at a documented path (e.g. in README or examples/)\",\n   265→        \"Workflow listens on all required events: issues, issue_comment, pull_request, pull_request_review, check_suite\",\n   266→        \"Workflow has correct permissions: issues: write, contents: write, pull-requests: write\",\n   267→        \"Single job that runs datashaman/kiln-action@v1 with anthropic_api_key input\",\n   268→        \"File includes comments explaining each trigger\"\n   269→      ],\n   270→      \"priority\": 17,\n   271→      \"passes\": false\n   272→    },\n   273→    {\n   274→      \"id\": \"US-018\",\n   275→      \"title\": \"CLAUDE.md Template for Kiln Users\",\n   276→      \"description\": \"As a user installing Kiln, I want a CLAUDE.md template that constrains all Kiln agents to safe behavior so that automation stays scoped and predictable.\",\n   277→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   278→        \"Template includes sections: Project description, Conventions (language, test runner, linting, commit style), Rules for Kiln Agents\",\n   279→        \"Default rules include: never modify workflows, never modify CLAUDE.md, always read spec before implementing, always run tests, keep changes scoped, comment on issue if blocked\",\n   280→        \"Template is clearly marked as a starting point that users should customize\",\n   281→        \"Provided in README and optionally as a standalone file (e.g. examples/CLAUDE.md)\"\n   282→      ],\n   283→      \"priority\": 18,\n   2