{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HBwusu9F3Biqnvwqv8nMru","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good - the approve-spec handler already exists and looks mostly complete. Let me review the acceptance criteria against the implementation:\n\n**AC Review for US-008:**\n1. **Triggers on pull_request_review.submitted where state is approved** - Handled by router ✓\n2. **Only runs on PRs with the kiln:spec label** - Handled by router (checks `:spec` label) ✓\n3. **Merges the spec PR via squash merge** - Done ✓\n4. **Extracts the issue number from the branch name (kiln/spec/issue-{number})** - Currently extracts from PR body using `Tracking issue: #(\\d+)` regex. The AC says \"branch name\". Let me fix this.\n5. **Applies kiln:implementing label to the linked issue** - Done via `transitionLabel` ✓\n6. **Removes kiln:spec-review label from the issue** - Done via `transitionLabel` (transitions from spec-review to implementing) ✓\n7. **Posts comment on the issue: implementation agent is starting** - Done ✓\n\nThe main issue is AC #4: the spec says to extract the issue number from the **branch name** (`kiln/spec/issue-{number}`), but the current implementation extracts it from the PR body. Let me update this to match the AC, using the branch name as the primary source (with PR body as fallback)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":252,"cache_read_input_tokens":40720,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":252},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c724d35f-7b14-4623-85ef-5de838552fab","uuid":"8b4e2826-7637-4ac7-964b-cdebfac5accb"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HBwusu9F3Biqnvwqv8nMru","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Wfo2i3xayGpYyQLUuowQMR","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/marlinf/Projects/datashaman/kiln-action/src/stages/approve-spec.ts","old_string":"  const issueMatch = (pr.body as string | undefined)?.match(\n    /Tracking issue: #(\\d+)/,\n  );\n  if (!issueMatch) {\n    core.warning(\"Could not find linked issue number in spec PR body.\");\n    return { status: \"success\" };\n  }\n\n  const issueNumber = parseInt(issueMatch[1], 10);","new_string":"  // Extract issue number from branch name (kiln/spec/issue-{number})\n  const branchName = pr.head?.ref as string | undefined;\n  const branchMatch = branchName?.match(/^kiln\\/spec\\/issue-(\\d+)$/);\n\n  // Fallback to PR body if branch name doesn't match\n  const bodyMatch = !branchMatch\n    ? (pr.body as string | undefined)?.match(/Tracking issue: #(\\d+)/)\n    : null;\n\n  const issueMatch = branchMatch || bodyMatch;\n  if (!issueMatch) {\n    core.warning(\"Could not find linked issue number in branch name or PR body.\");\n    return { status: \"success\" };\n  }\n\n  const issueNumber = parseInt(issueMatch[1], 10);"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":252,"cache_read_input_tokens":40720,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":252},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c724d35f-7b14-4623-85ef-5de838552fab","uuid":"67d20f6b-ed6c-4d42-8437-bfb9c62ce312"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wfo2i3xayGpYyQLUuowQMR","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/marlinf/Projects/datashaman/kiln-action/src/stages/approve-spec.ts has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c724d35f-7b14-4623-85ef-5de838552fab","uuid":"3105f647-dd52-49d4-ba4a-d7dd8647fa21","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/marlinf/Projects/datashaman/kiln-action/src/stages/approve-spec.ts","oldString":"  const issueMatch = (pr.body as string | undefined)?.match(\n    /Tracking issue: #(\\d+)/,\n  );\n  if (!issueMatch) {\n    core.warning(\"Could not find linked issue number in spec PR body.\");\n    return { status: \"success\" };\n  }\n\n  const issueNumber = parseInt(issueMatch[1], 10);","newString":"  // Extract issue number from branch name (kiln/spec/issue-{number})\n  const branchName = pr.head?.ref as string | undefined;\n  const branchMatch = branchName?.match(/^kiln\\/spec\\/issue-(\\d+)$/);\n\n  // Fallback to PR body if branch name doesn't match\n  const bodyMatch = !branchMatch\n    ? (pr.body as string | undefined)?.match(/Tracking issue: #(\\d+)/)\n    : null;\n\n  const issueMatch = branchMatch || bodyMatch;\n  if (!issueMatch) {\n    core.warning(\"Could not find linked issue number in branch name or PR body.\");\n    return { status: \"success\" };\n  }\n\n  const issueNumber = parseInt(issueMatch[1], 10);","originalFile":"import * as core from \"@actions/core\";\nimport { transitionLabel } from \"../labels\";\nimport { KilnContext, StageResult } from \"../types\";\n\nexport default async function approveSpec(\n  ctx: KilnContext,\n): Promise<StageResult> {\n  const { octokit, context, config } = ctx;\n  const pr = context.payload.pull_request!;\n  const prefix = config.labels?.prefix || \"kiln\";\n\n  core.info(`🔥 Approve Spec — PR #${pr.number}: ${pr.title}`);\n\n  try {\n    await octokit.rest.pulls.merge({\n      ...context.repo,\n      pull_number: pr.number,\n      merge_method: \"squash\",\n      commit_title: `${pr.title} (#${pr.number})`,\n    });\n    core.info(`Spec PR #${pr.number} merged.`);\n  } catch (error) {\n    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n    core.setFailed(`Failed to merge spec PR: ${message}`);\n    return { status: \"error\" };\n  }\n\n  const issueMatch = (pr.body as string | undefined)?.match(\n    /Tracking issue: #(\\d+)/,\n  );\n  if (!issueMatch) {\n    core.warning(\"Could not find linked issue number in spec PR body.\");\n    return { status: \"success\" };\n  }\n\n  const issueNumber = parseInt(issueMatch[1], 10);\n\n  await transitionLabel(\n    octokit,\n    context,\n    issueNumber,\n    \"spec-review\",\n    \"implementing\",\n    prefix,\n  );\n\n  await octokit.rest.issues.createComment({\n    ...context.repo,\n    issue_number: issueNumber,\n    body: `🔨 **Kiln** — Spec approved and merged. Starting implementation.`,\n  });\n\n  return { status: \"success\", nextStage: \"implement\" };\n}\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":25,"oldLines":11,"newStart":25,"newLines":18,"lines":["     return { status: \"error\" };","   }"," ","-  const issueMatch = (pr.body as string | undefined)?.match(","-    /Tracking issue: #(\\d+)/,","-  );","+  // Extract issue number from branch name (kiln/spec/issue-{number})","+  const branchName = pr.head?.ref as string | undefined;","+  const branchMatch = branchName?.match(/^kiln\\/spec\\/issue-(\\d+)$/);","+","+  // Fallback to PR body if branch name doesn't match","+  const bodyMatch = !branchMatch","+    ? (pr.body as string | undefined)?.match(/Tracking issue: #(\\d+)/)","+    : null;","+","+  const issueMatch = branchMatch || bodyMatch;","   if (!issueMatch) {","-    core.warning(\"Could not find linked issue number in spec PR body.\");","+    core.warning(\"Could not find linked issue number in branch name or PR body.\");","     return { status: \"success\" };","   }"," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
